RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 4 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TORRID TOMMY cleared rivals on the backstretch, continued clear on the turn and extended lead into the lane, implored by rider to dig in late to just last. AWESOME HEIGHTS stalked pace along the inside on the backstretch, continued in a good spot on the turn, launched rally along the inside, and gained to the wire to just miss under a strong drive. HOT PURSUIT chased leader in between rivals three deep on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, gained on leader to the wire while being outclosed by inside rival. RESTLESS RAMBLER broke out and bumped rival at the start, chased leader inside of three rivals, continued to hold rail on the turn, kept on in the lane to best the rest. TIZ INDY chased leader four deep on the backstretch, continued four wide on the turn, drifted into the lane and finished up one paced. STAY GOLDEN away a step slow and bumped back by rival at the start, settled well off the pace two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn and failed to launch a menacing bid. NEAH BAY bumped by inside rival at the start, chased clear leader in between rivals on the backstretch, failed to keep up with rivals on the turn and weakened in the lane. STREET BEHAVIOR broke cleanly, brushed with outside rival early, settled well off the pace along the rail and failed to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Restless Rambler
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out/bumped start, chased inside, bested rest

ENTRY.NAME: Neah Bay
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, chased between, weakened turn

ENTRY.NAME: Stay Golden
ENTRY.COMMENT: squeezed back start, settled 2wide, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Hot Pursuit
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC and Medina Lizbeth

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (QUARTER HORSE RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 4 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Maiden Races And Races For $2,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibi lity).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELUSIVE VIRTUE settled off the pace two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, found a seam entering the lane and finished strong the final hundred yards to get up right at the wire. VERMEER vied for lead outside of rival on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn, cleared rival entering the lane, stayed clear approaching the final sixteenth and nailed by surging outside rival at the wire. MALAKAI MOXIE broke in and bumped rival at the start, stalked pace three wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn and made belated progress in the four path in the final sixteenth. POTENTE ALBA reluctant to load, bumped by outside rival at the start, saved ground on the backstretch and turn and made mild progress in the lane. BANDSLAMMER vied for lead along the inside on the backstretch, continued along the inside on the turn, failed to keep up with rival and outfinished in the lane. CHIEF EAGLE EYE chased duo along the inside on the backstretch, saved ground on the turn, eased out and in range entering the lane and failed to respond to urging. BATTLING GERVINHO tracked duo two wide on the backstretch, continued two wide on the turn and tired entering the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Chief Eagle Eye
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased duo inside, in range 4path, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Potente Alba
ENTRY.COMMENT: reluctant to load, bumped start, inside, mildy
